Citations
Date:  0/0/1954
Source:  Take My Tip
Author:  JOURNET
Vol / Page:  77
Edition:
Quote:  Should Z [a horse] win his race he is said to have struck form. Should Z lose his race, especially when you have backed him, he is said to have run like a hairy goat, another foolish term as hairy goats are reputedly both agile and swift.
